venue.name: Ah Heng Curry Chicken Bee Hoon Mee 亚王咖喱鸡米粉面

tip.text: Ordered way too much food but it was seriously delicious. Half bo ssaam is already a whole lot of food for 5 people so no need to order too many other heavy dishes. Service needs to shape up though.
Get here early or else they do sell out (we lined up at 9 and ate at 1 on a Tuesday). Brisket and Pork ribs are winners and the banana bourbon pie is also a dark horse so get it!!
Lines are long and service is slow but it's really delicious. Beware that food will sell out.

formattedAddress: N. Highland Ave. (at E. El Paso St.)

tip.text: Service is slow since it's typically just one person making the drinks food/working the cashier/making the toasts but it's a must do in Marfa. The seasonal menu items all sound amazing.
Really delicious even though it's in the middle of nowhere. Great stop on the way to Marfa from Austin :)
Long list of beers but the blurbs for each are fun to read. Live music in the outside back area is great.
